@startuml
title Git-Auth-Proxy: Security and Deployment Flow

actor "Git Client" as Client
participant "Proxy Server\n(Gin)" as Proxy
participant "Token Extractor" as TokenExt
participant "Authorizer" as Auth
participant "Provider\n(GitHub/Azure DevOps)" as Provider
participant "Kubernetes API" as K8s
database "Kubernetes Secrets" as Secrets
participant "Token Writer" as TokenWriter
participant "Metrics Endpoint" as Metrics

== Deployment & Initialization Phase ==
activate Proxy
Proxy -> Proxy: Parse arguments\n& setup logging
Proxy -> Proxy: Load configuration\n(organizations, repos, namespaces)
Proxy -> Auth: NewAuthorizer(config)
activate Auth
Auth -> Provider: Initialize providers\n(GitHub/Azure DevOps)
activate Provider
Provider --> Auth: Provider instances
deactivate Provider
Auth --> Proxy: Authorizer instance
deactivate Auth

Proxy -> TokenWriter: Initialize TokenWriter
activate TokenWriter
TokenWriter -> K8s: Setup Kubernetes client
activate K8s
K8s --> TokenWriter: Client ready
TokenWriter -> K8s: Start Secret informer\n(watch for changes)
K8s --> TokenWriter: Informer active
deactivate K8s
TokenWriter --> Proxy: TokenWriter ready
deactivate TokenWriter

Proxy -> Proxy: Start metrics server
Proxy -> Proxy: Start proxy server
note right of Proxy
  Multi-stage Docker build:
  - Builder: Compile Go code
  - Runtime: Distroless image
  (minimized attack surface)
end note

== Token Management Phase ==
TokenWriter -> K8s: Monitor Secret changes
activate K8s
K8s -> TokenWriter: Secret created/updated
activate TokenWriter
TokenWriter -> Secrets: Store repository tokens\n(namespace-scoped)
activate Secrets
Secrets --> TokenWriter: Token stored
deactivate Secrets
TokenWriter --> K8s: Acknowledge
deactivate TokenWriter
deactivate K8s

== Authentication & Authorization Phase ==
Client -> Proxy: Git clone request\n(HTTPS with token)
activate Proxy
Proxy -> TokenExt: Extract token from request
activate TokenExt
TokenExt -> TokenExt: Parse Authorization header\nor query parameter
TokenExt --> Proxy: Extracted token
deactivate TokenExt

Proxy -> Auth: Validate token & authorize
activate Auth
Auth -> Auth: Check token against\nrequested repository
Auth -> Secrets: Verify token exists\nfor namespace/repo
activate Secrets
Secrets --> Auth: Token validation result
deactivate Secrets

alt Token Valid
    Auth --> Proxy: Authorization granted
    deactivate Auth
    Proxy -> Provider: Forward request with\nprovider credentials
    activate Provider
    Provider -> Provider: Generate authorization header\n(GitHub App token or PAT)
    Provider -> Provider: Construct API endpoint

    alt GitHub Provider
        Provider -> Provider: Use GitHub App installation\n(ghinstallation)
    else Azure DevOps Provider
        Provider -> Provider: Use Azure DevOps PAT
    end

    Provider -> Provider: Forward to Git provider
    note right of Provider
      Security: Provider-specific
      authentication tokens are
      never exposed to client
    end note
    Provider --> Proxy: Git provider response
    deactivate Provider
    Proxy --> Client: Repository data

else Token Invalid
    Auth --> Proxy: Authorization denied
    Proxy --> Client: 401 Unauthorized
    note right of Client
      Security: Multi-tenant isolation
      via namespace-scoped tokens
    end note
end

deactivate Proxy

== Monitoring Phase ==
Metrics -> Metrics: Expose Prometheus metrics
note right of Metrics
  Metrics include:
  - Request counts
  - Authorization success/failure
  - Token validation latency
end note

== Token Synchronization ==
TokenWriter -> K8s: Listen for Secret events
activate K8s
K8s -> TokenWriter: Secret deleted
activate TokenWriter
TokenWriter -> Auth: Remove token from authorizer
activate Auth
Auth -> Auth: Update endpoint permissions
Auth --> TokenWriter: Token removed
deactivate Auth
TokenWriter --> K8s: Acknowledge deletion
deactivate TokenWriter
deactivate K8s

@enduml
